  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Small-Scale Producers and Youth from Northern Honduras Producing Quality Cacao</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Due to increasing occupational demand in cacao cooperatives throughout Honduras, this project aims to sharpen the skills of cacao producers through our partner, APROCACAHO. Cacao producers will receive training on agroforestry techniques, quality and flavor control, and the establishment of a cacao fermentation protocol to be able to position themselves as producers of a Grade A cacao. The goals of the project are:  Cocoa producers have the skills to manage crops under agroforestry models through teaching, learning-by-doing and applying technological tools that accompany the training processes.  Leaders of cooperatives process and negotiate their quality A cacao to markets differentiated by its quality and flavor origin</narrative>
  </description>
